# Section 4. Programmability (14 pts)

1. 17.Find My Ride

Create a **user defined function** with the name **udf\_CheckForVehicle(@townName****, **** @seatsNumber****)** that receives a **town&#39;s name** and a **seats number** and checks if there is **any vehicle** with the **given seats** at an **office** of the **given**** town**.

- If **there is** a **vehicle** print the **output** in the following **format** : &quot; **OfficeName - Model**&quot;.
- If there is no vehicle found print the following message: &quot;NO SUCH VEHICLE FOUND&quot;
- If there is **more than one** vehicle available **order** the results by **office name**** ascending **and** return **the** first ****one**

Parameters:

- Town&#39;s name
- Seats number

### Example usage:

| **Query** |
| --- |
| **SELECT**** dbo. ****udf\_ CheckForVehicle**** (&#39;La Escondida&#39;, 9)** |
| **Id** | **FirstName** | **LastName** | **ReportsCount** |
| Green, Jaskolski and Blick - TL |

1. 18.Move a Vehicle

Create a **user defined stored procedure** with the name **usp\_MoveVehicle**** ( ****@vehicleId**** , **** @officeId****)**that receives a **vehicle&#39;s Id** and an **office&#39;s**** Id **and changes the vehicle&#39;s** OfficeId **to the given value** only if **there are** free ****ParkingPlaces** in the **given office**. If the move is not successful **rollback** any changes and throw an **exception** with message: &quot;Not enough room in this office!&quot;.

Parameters:

- Vehicle&#39;s Id
- Office&#39;s Id

### Example usage:

| **Query** |
| --- |
| **EXEC**  **usp\_MoveVehicle**** 7 ****,**  **32**** ; ****SELECT**  **OfficeId**  **FROM**  **Vehicles**  **WHERE**  **Id**  **=**  **7** |
| **Response** |
| 32 |

1. 19.Move the Tally

Create a **trigger** which adds the Total Mileage from an order to the Mileage of the vehicle from that order.

**IMPORTANT** : **Total Mileage** should be **added** to the **Mileage** of the vehicle **only** when it is **given** a **value** for the **first**** time **i.e. the trigger should** not ****get fired** if the **Total Mileage** in an order is **edited**** after **it is** already ****having** a **value**.

### Example usage:

| **Query** |
| --- |
| **UPDATE**  **Orders**** SET ****TotalMileage**  **=**  **100**** WHERE **** Id **** = **** 40 ****;** |
| **Response** |
| (1 row affected)(1 row affected) |
